  <title>Christian Aid:Empowerment for Health &amp; Livelihoods</title>
  <description>This project will work in the district of Karonga (northern Malawi) to raise awareness of the issues surrounding HIV through youth-led theatre, music and performance art. Activities will include: treatment, care and support for at least 600 people with HIV to include support groups and access to quality services; working with community members including religious leaders and youth to improve knowledge, attitudes and practices through outreach programmes; providing training in conservation farming to support food production; and providing training on advocacy at district level to raise awareness of vulnerable and at risk groups and improve access to quality HIV/AIDS related services. It builds on existing Scottish Government projects on community work around HIV/AIDS awareness by Christian Aid .</description>
